text:
colgo l'occasione della giornata mondiale contro la violenza sulle donne per dirvi che giovedì prossimo inaugura femminismi manifesti, esposizione collettiva per la quale 28 illustratrici hanno rielaborato altrettanti manifesti storici femministi. 
ho contribuito volentieri con un lavoro che verrà esposto insieme a quello di tante colleghe e amiche davvero in gamba. •
femminismi manifesti

da non una di meno vicenza.

text: en cette journée internationale pour l'élimination des violences faites aux femmes, j'emprunte cette puissante photographie de @lesjouesrouges pour @liberationfr pour réaffirmer mon engagement contre les violences sexistes et sexuelles. hier 50 000 femmes et hommes ont marché dans les rues françaises, uni.e.s par ce combat et vers le même objectif: que ces violences soient nommées, punies, éliminées. car ces violences sont des coups portés sur chaque femme, chaque jour. on m'a souvent demandé pourquoi j'utilisais le mot "harcèlement" pour les dénoncer, notamment à travers mon oeuvre immersive #monpremierharcelement. parce que ces violences sont quotidiennes et répétitives, que les survivantes (que je préfère à "victimes") y font face chaque jour dans la rue, la famille, au travail, sur le net, dans les institutions ... ce combat est collectif et j'y contribue en donnant la parole à 12 femmes qui m'ont raconté leur premier souvenir de harcèlement et dont les récits mêlés accompagnent les portraits fragmentés. cette installation artistique est à voir à partir de demain et pour une semaine dans le péristyle de l'hotel de ville de @villedavignon. merci à ces femmes de m'avoir offert leur histoire, merci à la ville d'avignon de contribuer à faire entendre leur voix. le combat continue. #noustoutes @noustoutes2411 #nousaussi #metoo #powerfulwomen #stopharassment #stopwomenviolence #sexism #streetharassment #cyberharcelement #rasleviol #feministartist #feministart

text:
"believe women" is not the same as saying "women never lie" but we currently have a culture in which the first reaction is "she's lying." the first reaction should always be "we believe her", and until there is a good reason not to, we must all support her. ~
so, at the start of @unwomen 16 days of activism we're making a pledge:
we will listen to survivors
we will stand up for justice
we will say #heartmetoo ~
1 in 3 women experiences violence in their lifetime. join us in saying no to violence against women and girls, and say we will #believewomen.
~
#orangetheworld #orangeurworld #endvaw #16days #metoo #whatnext

text:
hoy 25 de noviembre es el día mundial contra la violencia de género, un aspecto que sigue estando presente con múltiples vestigios de este, ya sea en forma de agresiones, abusos y como datos más espeluznantes: las muertes que cada año se cobran en nuestro país. 
sin embargo, también existen otras formas más sutiles, en ocasiones imperceptibles, que causan daño en quien lo padece y los de su alrededor. son formas sibilinas y silenciosas, en muchas ocasiones normalizadas, consentidas y, conocidas con el término de micromachismos, caldo de cultivo de violencia machista, de las que ninguna estamos inmunes de experimentar. algunos ejemplos de ello serian: ✔️la brecha salarial. ✔️el techo de cristal.
✔️conciliación familiar. ✔️uso desigual de las tareas domésticas.
✔️uso sexista del lenguaje.
✔️uso del espacio público.
✔️hipersexualización de la mujer en los medios públicos y privados.
y un largo etcétera.... si deseáis profundizar más sobre el tema os invito a leer mi nuevo post para mi blog donde os hablo acerca de ello.
➡️www.presbiciaemocional.com 💭 la educación afectivo sexual es imprescindible si queremos un cambio.

text:
過去一年，各地出現了種種如 #metoo 、 #timesup 、 #balancetonporc 、 #niunamenos 等草根以至全球性的反擊性暴力行動。在#國際終止女性受暴日（11月25日），我們除了希望感謝在過去一年來曾踏於發聲的前線、以自身經歷帶來社會改變、捍衛人權的幸存者外，亦希望大眾的注意力能遍及遠離新聞以致社交媒體的性暴力幸存者。

橫跨社會階層、種族及年齡，全球每三位女性就有一位曾經歷暴力對待，在當中就有大量的幸存者沒有把自己的故事放進 #metoo 地圖裏的發聲能力。幸存並離開暴力，是一個漫長及複雜的過程。

這一年來，是幸存者們的勇氣和行動為我們帶起社會關注，甚至引發制度的改變；風雨蘭會繼續秉承服務裏的關心、了解、尊重及充權，適切地支援不同幸存者。

今天同是立法會九龍西地區補選，我們呼籲九西的選民踴躍投票，亦希望當選者能關注及支援性暴力幸存者，一同終止性暴力。

text: today is the international day for the elimination of violence against women. violence against women and girls is one of the most widespread violations of human rights and it persists due to the silence, shame and lack of education that surrounds it. these statistics are a few years old but the figures are not improving. in the uk, of the 113 women killed by men in england, wales and northern ireland in 2016, 85 died in their homes. 9 in 10 of the women killed, died at the hands of someone they knew. of these, 78 women were killed by their current or former intimate partner, three by their sons and five by another male family member. gender based violence is so entrenched in our society and starts the second the words ‘boys will be boys’ are uttered. i was going to post something about my own experiences of gender based violence but this isn’t about me. this is about every single woman and girl across the world who is at risk every single day. #internationaldayfortheeliminationofviolenceagainstwomen #16daysofactivism #endviolenceagainstwomen #endviolenceagainstwomenandgirls #endgenderbasedviolence #orangetheworld #hearmetoo #boyswillbeheldaccountablefortheiractions #metoo #listentowomen #believewomen #endchildmarriage #endfgm #endrapeculture

text:
today is november 25th, the international day for the elimination of violence against women which marks the first day of 16 day campaign to raise awareness on gender-based violence. the #orangetheworld movement has expanded globally through campaigns #metoo #timesup #niunamenos #notonemore #balancetonporc and many more reaching montenegro this year as well.

it's our duty to work against silence and impunity that allows violence against women to be pushed under the rug. in the following 16 days we will present a series of posters to help raise awareness and motivate everyone to speak up and fight this awful tendency to abuse women in their homes, workplace and public places. 
this is the time to change. spread the word, break the silence. ⚖️📢🕛

text:
sono state 106 le donne uccise nel nostro paese nei primi dieci mesi del 2018, secondo i dati diffusi da eures per la giornata internazionale contro la violenza sulle donne del 25 novembre. le violenze avvengono in famiglia per il 70,2 per cento dei casi e all’interno della coppia. eures segnala un aumento progressivo dell’età media delle vittime, sopra i 52 anni. non sono solo giovani ragazze che hanno chiuso una storia, sono mogli e madri. oltre un terzo arrivano dopo denunce inascoltate e dopo ripetute violenze fisiche e psicologiche.
è il nord la zona più a rischio, seguito da sud e centro. il maggior numero di femminicidi è in lombardia (24 nel 2017, pari al 17 per cento del totale, di cui 17 familiari) davanti a lazio (roma è in testa come area metropolitana più pericolosa), puglia, campania, veneto ed emilia romagna.
sono decine le associazioni che si occupano delle donne che hanno subito violenza in italia o che sono vittime di maltrattamenti. ci sono centri locali e associazioni nazionali come il telefono rosa, che risponde allo 06-37518282, la casa delle donne per non subire violenza e dire, donne in rete per non subire violenza, che collega le organizzazioni sul territorio. le donne che si sono rivolte ai centri antiviolenza nel 2017 sono state 49.152, di queste 29.227 hanno iniziato un percorso di accompagnamento. il 26,9% delle donne che si rivolgono ai centri sono straniere e il 63,7% ha figli, minorenni in più del 70% dei casi. sono i dati raccolti dall’istat sui servizi offerti dai centri antiviolenza, in collaborazione con il dipartimento per le pari opportunità le regioni e il cnr. ( lavoro di @alagooon)
.
.
.

text:
leffest - day 9: touch me not (directed by adina pintilie)
this is one of the most touching and moving experiences of the year. touch me not is a reflection on intimacy, sexuality, sensuality, and our relationship with our bodies. it's a film that puts in question our societal norms of what is an ideal body and ideal sexuality. we are put face to face with bodies that go against what is considered beautiful and shown the beauty in them. the first thing we immediately see when the film start is the naked body of a man, and that sets the tone to that film. this is one of the most important films of the year and i think everyone should see it, even if you are uncomfortable with nudity or highly explicit sex scenes (consider this as a disclaimer). this film was made to make people uncomfortable and that's why i think, even if you are uncomfortable with these things, you should watch it. this is because it pushes our boundaries and changes the way we see these issues (it surely changed a lot of my views on a lot of things). it's one of the most liberating experiences of the year. it's beautifully directed, and everyone of the characters is simply unforgettable and will definitely stay with you.  touch me not is a necessary film in an age when we tend to get more and more distanced from our bodies. it's a necessary film in this #metoo moment. touch me not is one of the most powerful statements in this time when sexuality is such a sensitive subject, especially related to consent and identity. this is definitely a film that should be watched by everyone in order to open a freer and more understanding dialogue.
name: Jasmim Talks Cinema

text:
una-se pelo fim da violência contra as mulheres
#16diasdeativismo #onu

a comemoração oficial da onu do dia internacional pela eliminação da violência contra as mulheres, 25 de novembro, ocorreu na última segunda-feira (19/11), na sede das nações unidas, em nova iorque. o ato reuniu sobreviventes da violência de gênero e ativistas em torno do tema “pinte o mundo de laranja: #meescutetambém” (#hearmetoo #escúchametambién), acentuando as sua vozes e o trabalho pelo fim da violência contra mulheres e meninas.

a secretária-adjunta da onu e diretora executiva da onu mulheres, phumzile mlambo-ngcuka, frisou que “é responsabilidade coletiva que o mundo seja um lugar melhor e mais seguro para mulheres e meninas”. representando ativistas, daniela elizabeth giuliano expressou a autonomia das mulheres e a relação que esperam das instituições e das pessoas: “eu quero ser ouvida. eu tenho direitos”. pesquisas revelam que a pandemia da violência contra as mulheres e meninas afeta uma em cada três mulheres em algum momento da sua vida. este não é um fenômeno recente. nos últimos meses, movimentações globais têm trazido o tema à tona a partir da determinação e da coragem de ativistas e sobreviventes, como observado em conversas nas redes sociais, reunidas pelas hastags #metoo”, “#timesup”, “#balancetonporc”, “#niunamenos”, #metooindia e “hollaback!”. ao mesmo tempo em que a visibilidade pública é percebida em diferentes lugares do mundo sobre a ação da violência de gênero, são identificadas movimentações contrárias aos direitos das mulheres, defensoras de direitos bumanos e espaço civil que ameaçam os progressos. as duas tendências apontam para uma realidade: nenhum país, nenhuma organização está imune ao abuso sexual e à violência e mulheres e meninas de todo o mundo ainda experimentam abuso e violência com base em gênero.

fonte: www.onumulheres.org.br
#dialaranja #bastadeviolencia #conectidea #justiçasocial #ods5

text: "nel 2017 - secondo i dati raccolti dall'istat, che per la prima volta ha svolto l'indagine sui servizi offerti dai centri antiviolenza, in collaborazione con il dipartimento per le pari opportunità le regioni e il consiglio nazionale della ricerca - le donne che si sono rivolte ai centri antiviolenza sono state 49.152, 29.227 delle quali hanno iniziato un percorso di uscita dal tunnel dei maltrattamenti. il 26,9% delle vittime che si rivolgono ai centri sono straniere e il 63,7% ha figli, minorenni in più del 70% dei casi." "da gennaio a ottobre sono state oltre 70 le donne uccise per mano di chi diceva di 'amarle'. da gennaio a fine luglio sono state 1.646 le italiane e 595 le straniere che hanno presentato denuncia per stupro. l'istat stima che siano 1 milione 404mila le donne che hanno subito molestie fisiche o ricatti sessuali sul posto di lavoro da parte di un collega o del datore di lavoro. incalcolabili gli episodi di sessismo, che permeano la vita delle donne: obbligare una donna a cambiare strada perché davanti a quel bar le dicono battute oscene, subire apprezzamenti non graditi sul proprio corpo o su come è vestita, la scelta delle aziende di assumere più uomini che donne, il divario salariale tra uomo e donna, l'incessante prova delle donne per dimostrare la propria competenza e professionalità, il carico del lavoro di cura che pesa quasi totalmente sulle donne, le immagini pubblicitarie che schiacciano le donne in ruoli stereotipati, spesso umilianti". #nonènormalechesianormale #25novembre #stopviolence #nonunadimeno #woman #stopviolenceagainstwomen #femminicidio #sensibilizzazione #metoo #donne #stopviolence #feminist #feminism

text:
full disclosure.
i had a more "instagram-ish" photo to post than this one 🙄... one where my hair was brushed, my feet clean, my baby flashing his million dollar dimples at the camera (because i poked him obvs) and flowers scattered around us like we were in a bloody disney movie.
it was perfection 💁‍♀️
.
but lets get real... i'm not bambi nor do birds fly around me when i sing (not intentionally anyway 🙄) today billy boy was your run of the mill stage 5 clinger. there was crying, drooling, banging fists, latching to legs, more crying and attempts to gouge my eyes out with his iron grip. he also refused to eat anything but arrowroot biscuits all day 🤷‍♀️
don't be mistaken... me, sitting here, was an act of desperation (check the face ☝🏻😅) as it seems the only thing that stops my baby crying is leaves and clumps of grass.
checkmate billy, checkmate.

x x

text:
me too : india.

after tanushree dutta statement, many women have raised their voices. i when threw the me too india page and i read about this two women, who have released long statement about their traumatic past. vinta nanda, producer and writer, accused alok nath of rapping and brutalised her 20 years ago. she realised a long post in facebook (available on me too india). actor saloni chopra, have faced physical abused and sexism. she wrote about filmmakers sajid khan (housefull, himmatawal), vikas bahl (queen) and actor zain durrani. her post is on medium.com and watch her interview on zoom youtube channel.
.
🇫🇷.
.
après la déclaration de l’actrice tanushree dutta, de nombreuses femmes se sont exprimés. je suis allée sur la page me too india et je voulais partager le post de ses deux femmes qui ont chacune publié une longue déclaration sur ce qu'elles ont subi. vinta nanda, productrice et écrivaine, a accusé l’acteur alok nath de l'avoir violé et brutalisé il y a 20 ans. elle a réalisé un long post sur facebook (disponible sur la page me too india). quant à l’atrice saloni chopra, elle a subit des abus physiques et sexiste. elle a écrit sur les cinéastes sajid khan (housefull, himmatawal), vikas bahl (queen) et l'acteur zain durrani. son article est sur medium.com et regardez son interview sur la chaîne zoom youtube.

#bollywood #hindicinema #indiancinema #film #movie #cinema #metoo #salonichopra #vintananda #india

text:
thanks @archanaapania for keeping the conversation alive on @radiocityindia with #streedum. 
the #metoo movement must not become a passing fad, or a stand-off between men & women. we are all on the same side. it's as simple as good v/s evil and evil comes in many guises - one of which is to divide and conquer. i want to address this question that has been raised, about what is, or isn't appropriate behavior. when it comes to sexual harassment in the work place, it can be defined as any sexual behavior that makes someone uncomfortable or hinders them from properly doing their job. a comprehensive definition is given below. but to answer your question archana, i don't think a woman needs to issue a warning before taking action, if she has been harassed. it is her prerogative to escalate it immediately. which is why this question of what is "ok", or "what will put me in the #metoo shitlist" that men are asking themselves (and us) is such an important one to address. stay tuned for my blog... i'm going to dive deep.

what is sexual harassment? 
sexual harassment is unwelcome sexual behaviour, which could be expected to make a person feel offended, humiliated or intimidated. it can be physical, verbal or written.

sexual harassment is not consensual interaction, flirtation or friendship. sexual harassment is not behaviour that is mutually agreed upon.

sexual harassment is covered in the workplace when it happens:
📃
- at work
- at work-related events or where people are carrying out work-related functions
- between people sharing the same workplace
- a single incident is enough to constitute sexual harassment – it doesn’t have to be repeated.

men experience sexual harassment but it disproportionately affects women, especially in the workplace. (the australian human rights commission reported that 1 in 5 women experience sexual harassment in the workplace at some time.) 💔

sexual harassment is unwelcome sexual behaviour, which could be expected to make a person feel offended, humiliated or intimidated. it can be physical, verbal or written.

sexual harassment is not consensual interaction, flirtation or friendship. sexual harassment is not behaviour that is mutually agreed upon.

sexual harassment is covered in the workplace when it happens:
📃
- at work
- at work-related events or where people are carrying out work-related functions
- between people sharing the same workplace
- a single incident is enough to constitute sexual harassment – it doesn’t have to be repeated.

men experience sexual harassment but it disproportionately affects women, especially in the workplace. (the australian human rights commission reported that 1 in 5 women experience sexual harassment in the workplace at some time.) 💔

.
vi kommer gå så långt som det krävs

.

vi kommer att gå så långt som det krävs 💪🏼💕
.
#repost @feministerna ・・・
f! inrättar minnesdag för patriarkatets offer 
ett år har passerat sedan #metoo slog ner i sverige. alla var överens. det var oacceptabelt, åtgärder måste vidtas.
men, som oftast i frågor som rör jämställdhet och feminism, är steget från ord till handling oerhört långt. ett antal symboliska justeringar gjordes i regeringens budget, däremot lyser genomgripande reformer eller myndighetsdirektiv med sin frånvaro.

istället är det just nu snarare en backlash som sticker ut mest i det offentliga samtalet. debatten domineras av kränkta män, en nyväckt konservativ våg av röster som drömmer om hemmafrutillvaro och okunnigt hummande om ”genusflum”, samt den återkommande häpnadsväckande åsikten att ”det har gått för långt”, med #metoo, med jämställdheten, med mänskliga rättigheter.

som om vittnesmålen försvunnit i en kollektiv minnesförlust. feministiskt initiativ har inte glömt. därför gör vi nu den 8 november till en nationell minnesdag och dedicerar hela månaden november till att minnas, hedra och visa uppskattning för de många metoo-uppropen”, skriver gita nabavi och gudrun schyman. →läs hela artikeln här: https://www.svt.se/opinion/vi-kommer-att-ga-sa-langt-som-det-kravs?fbclid=iwar2hqhk2zb0xczynoa4ww-3wzvsr1o9lxmpk_oehjjdu6i62jfpxcoyp-yw

text_retweet:
.
#repost @time with @make_repost
・・・
it’s been eight years since south korean prosecutor seo ji-hyun says she was sexually harassed, but it’s still painful to recall. “for a long time, i tortured myself by blaming myself for everything,” she tells time in seoul. seo alleges she was repeatedly groped at a funeral by a senior male colleague, while the country’s justice minister sat nearby, in 2010. seo reported the incident to her managers shortly after, but was subjected to performance audits that she describes as unfair, and assigned to a lower level branch outside seoul—a move she says did not match her strong track record at work. last fall, seo watched as #metoo took off. she began to grasp how widespread sexual harassment and assault were. seo added her voice to the rising global chorus in january, sharing her experience in an open letter on her workplace intranet and signing it with #metoo. within a few hours of posting, she says the justice department said her statement was false and refused to issue an apology. (the ministry of justice did not respond to time’s repeated requests for comment on the case; seo’s alleged harasser has denied the charge, saying he was too drunk at the time to recall what happened.) that evening, seo spoke on one of south korea’s most influential news programs. her words resonated: she is widely credited with kick-starting south korea’s version of the movement. women’s rights activists and survivors across asia have seen the global reckoning confronting sexual harassment, assault and abuse as a chance to shape their own national conversations about gender #inequality, amid intense backlash and great personal risk. but the broader cultural impact of speaking out in such challenging environments is creating a groundswell of support and solidarity. photograph by @timfranco for time. video by @ariahychen for time

text: war is over, take these men off your pedestal just bc someone is talented or in some power position to do “great things” for society does not mean they haven’t been awful too.. they are a whole, real person with demons and they’ve been hurt and hurt people too.. let us tell the truth so healing can happen for all involved #metoo #truth #shadow #love #peace #unity #ageofaquarius ...................................................................... “i used to be cruel to my woman, i beat her and kept her apart from the things that she loved’ ..that was me. i used to be very cruel to my woman, and physically… any woman. i was a hitter. i couldn’t express myself and i hit. i fought men and i hit women… but i sincerely believe in love and peace. i am a violent man who has learned not to be violent and regrets his violence. i will have to be a lot older before i can face in public how i treated women as a youngster.” -john lennon ..........................................……............................ “dad could talk about peace and love out loud to the world but he could never show it to the people who supposedly meant the most to him: his wife and son. how can you talk about peace and love and have a family in bits and pieces — no communication, adultery, divorce? you can’t do it, not if you’re being true and honest with yourself.” -john’s son, julian lennon

text:
#throwbackmonday 
opening cremony of national level 1 coaching trainning in puspitek (banten province) along with asdep @kemenpora bpk. herman chaniago. 
opening of national coaching trainning for level on 1 with 54 new coachs attetding it.

in the closing staments was underlined to the audience the importance of understading how to coach properly. i stated to the attendance from all over indonesia; that it is important to have a team to coach or a player to develope, and not only learning how to coach.

therefore, they have a moral duty when they return to thier province to develop that game of cricket (tournaments etc.) inorder for them to have a chance to coach a team. for that, they need to scout talents.

till today, cricket in indonesia has been introduced to more than 80.000 youths through out indonesia

development is a role of us all, from every layer of the game.

om jag svarar ”nytta”, så är det inte säkert att du vill köpa sex av mig. det är inte sexigt för dom där rikare torskarna att man skriver att man inte vill. oavsett vem du köper sex av, kommer det verka frivilligt. du kan försöka rättfärdiga att du har sex med någon som inte vill med att det var välgörenhet, att du annars inte får ligga eller att din fru inte släpper till. men du kan aldrig komma ifrån att det är dina pengar som gör att du får göra saker med min kropp. det finns inget nöje i det för mig. det är nytta. det är nöd. jag gör vad som helst för att klara min situation. om du vill träffa mig och betala x antal tusen och kräver analsex i gengäld är det något jag är beredd att göra. för jag skulle inte få några pengar om jag inte ställer upp. och det är inte sex att köpa någons kropp. det är ett sexuellt övergrepp och du kan aldrig veta vilka tvingande faktorer som gör att jag som hora säger ja, ler mot dig, är vänlig mot dig. det är desperat skådespel från mitt håll. och jag är inte den enda som säljer sex och vantrivs med det. så glöm aldrig att sexköp är en våldtäkt där offret får pengarna före övergreppet istället för efter. det är upp till dig nu att avgöra om du vill våldta någon eller inte. för nu vet du vad du betalar för. #utanskyddsnät #intedinhora #metoo #prostitution

text:
#biglittlelies is the best television series i've ever seen. i adore the women involved in this. what an impeccable cast. i can only hope and pray that one day i might work alongside these amazing actresses and actors (sorry i know they're gender neutralizing and referring to everyone as just 'actors' now but 'actress' sounds so elegant and proper to me!). if writing reviews (i don't like the idea of being a 'critic') but if it helps me get from point a to b i'll do it, and it might earn me some brownie points along the way.. lolol

so when i saw the pilot i'll admit my first thought was that despite the gorgeous production value, smart writing and stunning scenery - it seemed a little shallow. the quality problems of the upper echelon of monterey, ca. adult mean girls in norcal? real housewives of monterey? (i'm totally kidding.. and so exaggerating these presumptions i had) boy was i wrong. i've never been this wrong.

i was absolutely blindsided by the depth, poignancy, and unflinching humanity of the story. not to mention the urgently important themes and underlying messages once the layers of these delicately, lovingly crafted characters start peeling back. once the secrets and vulnerabilties of these women began to reveal themselves, i could not take my eyes off the screen & proceeded to binge watch the entire series in one day.

nicole kidman's performance here is the gravity that plunges audiences down the rabbit hole of human emotion. the other actresses are phenomenal too and the men compliment them well especially alexander skarsgaard who continues to blow my mind with his ever expanding range of characters and gender fluidity. he embodies masculinity for a new generation and era. he is fearsome yet gentle,  fearlessly in touch with his feminine side, and all the more masculine for it. as an actor and a man he portrays the best kind of confidence: the silent kind. silent confidence is infinitely more sexy than the loud, barking, boisterous macho man crowding today's 24 hour fitness locations and gawking at themselves in the mirror while pumping iron and yelling like animals unnecessarily as they do so.

anyway nicole kidman's (1/2 see comments below)
name: Nick Kavanaugh
tweet_full:
#biglittlelies is the best television series i have ever seen. i adore the women involved in this. what an impeccable cast. i can only hope and pray that one day i might work alongside these amazing actresses and actors (sorry i know they're gender neutralizing and referring to everyone as just 'actors' now but 'actress' sounds so elegant and proper to me!). if writing reviews (i do not like the idea of being a 'critic') but if it helps me get from point a to b i'll do it, and it might earn me some brownie points along the way.. lolol

so when i saw the pilot i'll admit my first thought was that despite the gorgeous production value, smart writing and stunning scenery - it seemed a little shallow. the quality problems of the upper echelon of monterey, ca. adult mean girls in norcal? real housewives of monterey? (i am totally kidding.. and so exaggerating these presumptions i had) boy was i wrong. i have never been this wrong.

i was absolutely blindsided by the depth, poigcy, and unflinching humanity of the story. not to mention the urgently important themes and underlying messages once the layers of these delicately, lovingly crafted characters start peeling back. once the secrets and vulnerabilties of these women began to reveal themselves, i could not take my eyes off the screen & proceeded to binge watch the entire series in one day.

nicole kidman's performance here is the gravity that plunges audiences down the rabbit hole of human emotion. the other actresses are phenomenal too and the men compliment them well especially alexander skarsgaard who continues to blow my mind with his ever expanding range of characters and gender fluidity. he embodies masculinity for a new generation and era. he is fearsome yet gentle,  fearlessly in touch with his feminine side, and all the more masculine for it. as an actor and a man he portrays the best kind of confidence: the silent kind. silent confidence is infinitely more sexy than the loud, barking, boisterous macho man crowding today's 24 hour fitness locations and gawking at themselves in the mirror while pumping iron and yelling like animals unnecessarily as they do so.

anyway nicole kidman's (1/2 see comments below)

text: porque educação sexual de qualidade não é doutrinação, mas sim uma formação necessária para uma vivência sadia da sexualidade, que engloba aspectos como acolhimento, conhecimento sobre seu corpo, gênero, diversidade, prevenção e tudo mais que envolve amor, prazer e respeito. "mais do que ensinar sobre métodos contraceptivos e os aspectos biológicos dos órgãos sexuais, os professores alemães também discutem igualdade de gênero, valores sociais e emoções relacionadas à sexualidade e a relacionamentos. a abordagem do tema é holística, considerando os diferentes aspectos da sexualidade humana. por isso, na maioria dos estados, a educação sexual é integrada a outras disciplinas, como ética, biologia, religião e ciências sociais. em alguns estados, há disciplinas específicas de educação sexual nas escolas." #sexualidade #saudesexual #educacao #educacaosexual #educarprevine #educacaocomecaemcasa #sexualidadeetabu #tabus #mitos #diganao #metoo #relacionamentosabusivos #abusoinfantil #rape #estupro #diganaoaviolencia #prazeremsaber

text:
opening cremony of national level 1 coaching trainning in puspitek (banten province) by asdep @kemenpora  bok. herman chaniago @hermanchaniago64  and vice chairman of pci mr. abhiram singh yadav @asycentre

opening of national coaching trainning for level on 1 with 54 new coachs attetding it.

in the closing staments was underlined to the audience the importance of understading how to coach properly. i stated to the attendance from all over indonesia; that it is important to have a team to coach or a player to develope, and not only learning how to coach.

therefore, they have a moral duty when they return to thier province to develop that game of cricket (tournaments etc.) inorder for them to have a chance to coach a team. for that, they need to scout talents.

till today, cricket in indonesia has been introduced to more than 80.000 youths through out indonesia

development is a role of us all, from every layer of the game.

text: jupiter enters sagittarius. 4:38am pst 11/8/18. what a ride it’s been having the planet of excess & exposure in scorpio, the sign of what’s hidden underneath. we’ve done some digging in the dirty dirt for a cycle now it’s time for jupiter to return to it’s mutable home sign of sag. it’s time to think on what we’ve discovered. it’s time to grow a new philosophy around all we’ve unearthed. it’s time to consider how to rise up, up, and out from this place we’ve now found us in. are you ready for a shift? #metoo there is a call to contemplate a wild future where we don’t have boxes, only clear hexagons & crystal dodecahedrons...which are actually doorways thru to the great mystery. we must find laughter & joy in our uniqueness. we must step forward into the temple where the divine feminine and the divine masculine are held on high. we must open our hearts, minds & spirits; to be reminded of what makes humans great- our ability to ponder & speak. we must expand out of our nostalgia & begin a new quest, a study, a practice, a conversation. we must begin again from a place of truth. the potential for over-jupitering this jupiter transit is really real tho babes. make sure you have a tether to your grounding cord at all times. notice when you’re getting too wild. check in. jupiter is a gift but remember what they say about the gift horse? too much of a good thing can be a bad thing. moderation will be a good keyword- especially if your sag house is busy. but please don’t fear fun either. we’ve had a hard year babes. we did big healing werk. we deserve to let loose- it reminds us why we fight. go dance. i love you silly ponies. may you run forever free babes! 🐎 ♥️💋

text:
bannon wanted to use the sorts of aggressive messaging tactics usually reserved for geopolitical conflicts to move the us electorate further to the right, wylie said. he had already directed a series of anti-establishment, conservative documentary films and presided over the far-right website breitbart news, but cambridge analytica would mark another step in his overall ambitions to transform the nation.

with financial backing from hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer, bannon co-founded cambridge analytica in 2013 as the us-branch of strategic communication laboratories (scl) group, a british company that advertises how it has conducted "behavioral change" programs in more than 60 countries.

wylie described cambridge analytica as - steve bannon and robert mercer using a foreign, military contractor ... to use some of the same techniques that the military uses ... on the american electorate.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan and drew griffin
cnn

bannon wanted to use the sorts of aggressive messaging tactics usually reserved for geopolitical conflicts to move the us electorate further to the right, wylie said. he had already directed a series of anti-establishment, conservative documentary films and presided over the far-right website breitbart news, but cambridge analytica would mark another step in his overall ambitions to transform the nation.

with financial backing from hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer, bannon co-founded cambridge analytica in 2013 as the us-branch of strategic communication laboratories (scl) group, a british company that advertises how it has conducted "behavioral change" programs in more than 60 countries.

wylie described cambridge analytica as - steve bannon and robert mercer using a foreign, military contractor ... to use some of the same techniques that the military uses ... on the american electorate.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan and drew griffin
cnn

text:
wylie said that bannon's plans began to solidify in 2014, when cambridge analytica consulted various republican campaigns and pacs ahead of the midterm elections. the company began to test and apply its psychographics by using facebook data to model individuals' personality types in order to understand how to influence them.

documents show the john bolton super pac, which promoted candidates supported by recently appointed white house national security adviser john bolton, paid cambridge analytical $454,700 in 2014 for "behavioral microtargeting with psychographic messaging." those services included strategies that broke individual voters into "clusters" based on what messages would resonate with them.

wylie also said the company used focus groups and messaging trials in 2014 to test some of the concepts that became core themes of the trump campaign, such as "drain the swamp" and imagery of walls. "a lot of the narratives of the trump campaign were what we were testing in 2014," wylie said.

he added that bannon directly presided over much of the company's initial research. "everything that we were doing ultimately had to be passed up to bannon for approval," said wylie, who left the company in late 2014.

wylie said bannon would fly to london about once a month for company meetings, and during that time he came to understand bannon's ideology. "he really liked the idea of using a military-style approach to changing people's perceptions," wylie said.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan & drew griffin
cnn

text:
- bannon got it immediately. he believes in the whole andrew breitbart doctrine that politics is downstream from culture, so to change politics you need to change culture. and fashion trends are a useful proxy for that. trump is like a pair of uggs, or crocs, basically. so how do you get from people thinking ‘ugh. totally ugly’ to the moment when everyone is wearing them? that was the inflection point he was looking for.

is what cambridge analytica does akin to bullying? - i think it’s worse than bullying, christopher wylie says. - because people don’t necessarily know it’s being done to them. at least bullying respects the agency of people because they know. so it’s worse, because if you do not respect the agency of people, anything that you’re doing after that point is not conducive to a democracy. and fundamentally, information warfare is not conducive to democracy.

millions of people’s personal information was stolen and used to target them in ways they wouldn’t have seen, and couldn’t have known about, by a mercenary outfit, cambridge analytica, who, wylie says, “would work for anyone”. who would pitch to russian oil companies. would they subvert elections abroad on behalf of foreign governments?

it occurs to me to ask wylie this one night. - yes.

nato or non-nato? - either. i mean they’re mercenaries. they’ll work for pretty much anyone who pays.

it’s an incredible revelation. it also encapsulates all of the problems of outsourcing – at a global scale, with added cyberweapons. and in the middle of it all are the public – our intimate family connections, our “likes”, our crumbs of personal data, all sucked into a swirling black hole that’s expanding and growing and is now owned by a politically motivated billionaire.

carole cadwalladr
the guardian

is what cambridge analytica does akin to bullying? - i think it’s worse than bullying, christopher wylie says. - because people don’t necessarily know it’s being done to them. at least bullying respects the agency of people because they know. so it’s worse, because if you do not respect the agency of people, anything that you’re doing after that point is not conducive to a democracy. and fundamentally, information warfare is not conducive to democracy.

millions of people’s personal information was stolen and used to target them in ways they wouldn’t have seen, and couldn’t have known about, by a mercenary outfit, cambridge analytica, who, wylie says, “would work for anyone”. who would pitch to russian oil companies. would they subvert elections abroad on behalf of foreign governments?

it occurs to me to ask wylie this one night. - yes.

nato or non-nato? - either. i mean they’re mercenaries. they’ll work for pretty much anyone who pays.

it’s an incredible revelation. it also encapsulates all of the problems of outsourcing – at a global scale, with added cyberweapons. and in the middle of it all are the public – our intimate family connections, our “likes”, our crumbs of personal data, all sucked into a swirling black hole that’s expanding and growing and is now owned by a politically motivated billionaire.

carole cadwalladr
the guardian

mi lado de la experiencia internacional de miss earth:
- después de un año y medio de preparación para mi primer concurso de belleza; en el certamen de miss earth, estaba emocionado de volver a filipinas por sexta vez. la hospitalidad de los filipinos no se encuentra en ningún otro lugar. filipinas es como un segundo hogar para mí. me uní al concurso para marcar la diferencia y ser un modelo a seguir para quienes me rodean. disfruté de la mayoría del concurso, pero lo que no sabía es que un patrocinador específico del manila yacht club cambiaría la forma en que veo el espectáculo y los patrocinadores. el patrocinador que se llama amado s. cruz se convirtió en un problema para muchos de los delegados, incluido yo mismo. para concentrarme solamente en mí mismo, me apartaron varias veces para que me invitaran a boracay, a las islas privadas y a su casa, e insistí en que yo y "las mujeres latinas bailamos para él". competición en la que pude alejarlo, pero me dijo constantemente que no le contara a nadie sobre ninguno de los casos. en el club de yates de manila, amado s. cruz se aseguró de que los jefes de equipo y el personal de seguridad estuvieran separados en otra habitación, aquí es donde hizo que muchas chicas se sintieran incómodas. un grupo de nosotros abandonó la sala porque nos sentimos incómodos, pero amado s. cruz nos siguió e insistió en que nos quedáramos dentro para bailar con él. les pedimos a los gerentes de nuestro equipo que nos trajeran a los autobuses, lo que les llevó más de 20 minutos finalmente. más tarde esa noche, @missjaimeyvonne y @ miss.earth.england hablaron por teléfono con lorraine schuck, vicepresidenta de miss earth, quien les aseguró que amado s. cruz no participaría en ningún otro evento. desde el momento en que comenzó el concurso hasta la noche de la coronación, amado s. cruz estuvo presente en cada evento y cena a la que pudo asistir físicamente. dado que otros delegados han publicado, muchas otras reinas de los últimos años han manifestado el mismo comportamiento. quiero ayudar a poner fin a este patrocinador que está

text_retweet:
#repost @feministerna
• • • • •
f! inrättar minnesdag för patriarkatets offer 
ett år har passerat sedan #metoo slog ner i sverige. alla var överens. det var oacceptabelt, åtgärder måste vidtas.
men, som oftast i frågor som rör jämställdhet och feminism, är steget från ord till handling oerhört långt. ett antal symboliska justeringar gjordes i regeringens budget, däremot lyser genomgripande reformer eller myndighetsdirektiv med sin frånvaro.

istället är det just nu snarare en backlash som sticker ut mest i det offentliga samtalet. debatten domineras av kränkta män, en nyväckt konservativ våg av röster som drömmer om hemmafrutillvaro och okunnigt hummande om ”genusflum”, samt den återkommande häpnadsväckande åsikten att ”det har gått för långt”, med #metoo, med jämställdheten, med mänskliga rättigheter.

som om vittnesmålen försvunnit i en kollektiv minnesförlust. feministiskt initiativ har inte glömt. därför gör vi nu den 8 november till en nationell minnesdag och dedicerar hela månaden november till att minnas, hedra och visa uppskattning för de många metoo-uppropen”, skriver gita nabavi och gudrun schyman. →läs hela artikeln här: https://www.svt.se/opinion/vi-kommer-att-ga-sa-langt-som-det-kravs?fbclid=iwar2hqhk2zb0xczynoa4ww-3wzvsr1o9lxmpk_oehjjdu6i62jfpxcoyp-yw

text:
had an incredible time at the society for neuroscience conference these past few days. so grateful for and impressed by the dozens of  groundbreaking scientists who moonlight as activists! i was so happy to see panel discussions supporting diversity and sexual harassment prevention in addition to more specific lectures advocating for criminal justice reform, whether through reconsidering when a person becomes an “adult” or exploring the consequences of solitary confinement. we’re on the right path but there’s still work to be done to make science and inclusive space for researchers struggling with mental health, i would’ve liked to see a roundtable or special lecture on that. #sfn2019 ?

text:
#stopviolenceagainstwomen #metoo #stopviolence #humanrights #equality
...آقای فرشید مثقالی، نگار مسعودی و من
قصه "نگار" را همینجا بخوانید و برای خواندن قصه های مستند بیشتر به صفحه اش مراجعه کنید
 ١٧ سالم بود ، دختر شاد و سرزنده اي بودم و مثل همه آدمها توي اين سن عاشق پيشه.نمي دونم يادتون مياد يا نه ، توي اون سالها فيلم هاي خصوصي زيادي از جشن تولد و عروسي و... آدمها بيرون مي اومد و به شكل سي دي دست به دست ميشد و آدما انگار از اين سرك كشيدن بدون اجازه توي احوالات خصوصي ديگران لذت مي بردند و براشون مثل يك سرگرمي بود . دايي من هم يكي از تفريحاتش همين بود، دست بر قضا يك روز كه با دوستانش مشغول ديدن فيلم يك جشن تولد دخترونه بودن ، با خودش ميگه اِ اين كه نگاره!همون روز اين آدم اسلحه اي رو كه هميشه توي خونش داشته بر ميداره و مياد خونه ما ، نشسته بود توي حال خونه و پدر و مادرم رو صدا زد من هم بودم ، همه نشستيم ، دايي بنده... با افتخار كلتش رو در اورد و گذاشت وسط ، بعد از كلي توهين هاي جنسيتي گفت:"ديشب يه فيلم تولد ديدم كه تازه بيرون اومده،من همون شب كه فيلم رو ديدم داشتم ميامدم كه نگار رو بكشم ، ولي نشد ، شانس آورد، امروز با بقيه برادرا يعني دايي دوم من ... رفتيم خونه كسي كه فكر كردم تولد توي خونه اون بوده( چون چند وقت قبلش ما يك تولد دخترونه داشتيم) و بعد از اينكه حسابي اون دختر رو مورد ضرب و شتم قرار داديم و به گه خوردن انداختيمش فيلم رو نشستيم ديديم ،براي چند بار و متوجه شديم كه اصلا اون يك تولد ديگري بوده، خلاصه كه نگار خيلي شانس اورد كه نكشتمش" .
الان سالهاست كه ازاون ماجرا مي گذره و اون آدم هم توي فاميل محبوبيتش رو داره و داره زندگي عاديش رو ادامه ميده. اما من سالهاست كه با اين حفره عميق رواني زندگي ميكنم و رنج مي كشم ، رنجي كه وصف ناپذيره.
امروز كه ٣٣ ساله هستم و براي گرفتن حقم نيازي به حمايت خانواده ندارم دست به اقدامي زدم وكيل گرفتم و براي "اقدام به قتل" ازش شكايت كردم ، طبق صحبتهايي كه وكيلم باهاش داشته  گفته كه "اصلا پشيمون نيستم و اي كاش كه مي كشتمش".اين آدم و كساني مثل اون خطرناك هستن و باز هم ممكنه دست به چنين خشونتهايي بزنند،ميدونم كه كار سختيه و زمان مي بره چون خيلي سال ازش مي گذره ولي من كوتاه بيا نيستم ، نه فقط بخاطر خودم بلكه بخاطر هزاران زن مثل من كه مورد خشونت هاي جنسيتي قرار گرفته و مي گيرند.

 ١٧ سالم بود ، دختر شاد و سرزنده اي بودم و مثل همه آدمها توي اين سن عاشق پيشه.نمي دونم يادتون مياد يا نه ، توي اون سالها فيلم هاي خصوصي زيادي از جشن تولد و عروسي و... آدمها بيرون مي اومد و به شكل سي دي دست به دست ميشد و آدما انگار از اين سرك كشيدن بدون اجازه توي احوالات خصوصي ديگران لذت مي بردند و براشون مثل يك سرگرمي بود . دايي من هم يكي از تفريحاتش همين بود، دست بر قضا يك روز كه با دوستانش مشغول ديدن فيلم يك جشن تولد دخترونه بودن ، با خودش ميگه اِ اين كه نگاره!همون روز اين آدم اسلحه اي رو كه هميشه توي خونش داشته بر ميداره و مياد خونه ما ، نشسته بود توي حال خونه و پدر و مادرم رو صدا زد من هم بودم ، همه نشستيم ، دايي بنده... با افتخار كلتش رو در اورد و گذاشت وسط ، بعد از كلي توهين هاي جنسيتي گفت:"ديشب يه فيلم تولد ديدم كه تازه بيرون اومده،من همون شب كه فيلم رو ديدم داشتم ميامدم كه نگار رو بكشم ، ولي نشد ، شانس آورد، امروز با بقيه برادرا يعني دايي دوم من ... رفتيم خونه كسي كه فكر كردم تولد توي خونه اون بوده( چون چند وقت قبلش ما يك تولد دخترونه داشتيم) و بعد از اينكه حسابي اون دختر رو مورد ضرب و شتم قرار داديم و به گه خوردن انداختيمش فيلم رو نشستيم ديديم ،براي چند بار و متوجه شديم كه اصلا اون يك تولد ديگري بوده، خلاصه كه نگار خيلي شانس اورد كه نكشتمش" .
الان سالهاست كه ازاون ماجرا مي گذره و اون آدم هم توي فاميل محبوبيتش رو داره و داره زندگي عاديش رو ادامه ميده. اما من سالهاست كه با اين حفره عميق رواني زندگي ميكنم و رنج مي كشم ، رنجي كه وصف ناپذيره.
امروز كه ٣٣ ساله هستم و براي گرفتن حقم نيازي به حمايت خانواده ندارم دست به اقدامي زدم وكيل گرفتم و براي "اقدام به قتل" ازش شكايت كردم ، طبق صحبتهايي كه وكيلم باهاش داشته  گفته كه "اصلا پشيمون نيستم و اي كاش كه مي كشتمش".اين آدم و كساني مثل اون خطرناك هستن و باز هم ممكنه دست به چنين خشونتهايي بزنند،ميدونم كه كار سختيه و زمان مي بره چون خيلي سال ازش مي گذره ولي من كوتاه بيا نيستم ، نه فقط بخاطر خودم بلكه بخاطر هزاران زن مثل من كه مورد خشونت هاي جنسيتي قرار گرفته و مي گيرند.
نگار مسعودي١٤ آبان ١٣٩٧#زن_ستیزی #خشونت_علیه_زنان

text:
f! inrättar minnesdag för patriarkatets offer 
ett år har passerat sedan #metoo slog ner i sverige. alla var överens. det var oacceptabelt, åtgärder måste vidtas.
men, som oftast i frågor som rör jämställdhet och feminism, är steget från ord till handling oerhört långt. ett antal symboliska justeringar gjordes i regeringens budget, däremot lyser genomgripande reformer eller myndighetsdirektiv med sin frånvaro.

istället är det just nu snarare en backlash som sticker ut mest i det offentliga samtalet. debatten domineras av kränkta män, en nyväckt konservativ våg av röster som drömmer om hemmafrutillvaro och okunnigt hummande om ”genusflum”, samt den återkommande häpnadsväckande åsikten att ”det har gått för långt”, med #metoo, med jämställdheten, med mänskliga rättigheter.

som om vittnesmålen försvunnit i en kollektiv minnesförlust. feministiskt initiativ har inte glömt. därför gör vi nu den 8 november till en nationell minnesdag och dedicerar hela månaden november till att minnas, hedra och visa uppskattning för de många metoo-uppropen”, skriver gita nabavi och gudrun schyman. →läs hela artikeln här: https://www.svt.se/opinion/vi-kommer-att-ga-sa-langt-som-det-kravs?fbclid=iwar2hqhk2zb0xczynoa4ww-3wzvsr1o9lxmpk_oehjjdu6i62jfpxcoyp-yw

text:
idag, den 8 november, är det årsdagen för #tystnadtagning.

ett år sedan 703 skådespelare i sverige gick samman i ett gemensamt #metoo -upprop för att vittna om de sexuella övergrepp och trakasserier som de bevittnat och utsatts för i film- och teaterbranschen.

imorgon, den 9 november, kliver också ofelia upp ur bäcken och berättar sin historia.

vi reser oss. vi är en ny version. vi är 2.0.
era namn står i rött. vi stryker under. checkar av.
vi säger: titta vad ni fick oss att göra.
ni säger: världen går vidare.
en ny dag, ett nytt drama.
men inte för oss.
vi litar inte på någon och ni tror inte ens på oss.
vi reser oss igen. om och om igen. hela tiden.

text:
many common criticisms of #metoo focus on the ‘poor men’ who now have to watch their behaviour. it’s time to put the focus back where it’s needed – on women who have always faced harassment and never had the opportunity to speak up.

#metoo india has engulfed us in more ways than one. media – print and social – have ensured we are in the know of all stories of abuse and harassment, most of which were known in hush-hush conversations, while a few others shocked us!

but let us all acknowledge one fact: in more ways than one, the stories on workplace harassment have for long existed and then hidden and remained ensconced in personal accounts to counsellors, personal diaries, hr departments and in nightmares.

#metoo has been about spontaneous outpouring of harassment and abuse faced by women, but like all movements, soon enough it has seen massive criticism from diverse quarters as well, a few of which i will attempt to discuss and then debunk!

more on womensweb.in

#women #womenempowerment #womenempoweringwomen #workingwomen

text:
this past month has been full of subtle ups and downs that nevertheless leave me wiped out in engaging #churchdv. in the past month there has been movement as the leaders in my former congregation come to understand what abuse is. they are having conversations. doing lots of learning and coming to see how the actions and inactions of my former partner fit into the cycle of domination and degradation of intimate partner abuse. they've offered to foot the bill for my personal therapy. (no thanks.) ¶  but there has been resistance to advocating for me and restoring me to fellowship because it would require public acknowledgement of what happened. as so many have said before, silence favors the abusive. silence is all they ask for. i watch, deflated, as the opportunity is lost to reach previous victims and future victims -- all of which would require preaching, ministering, educating, and talking to those who suffer directly. for those of us who grew up in dv households or have experienced first-hand abuse, we know the real trauma comes from not finding a route of escape. you cannot escape when you don't know you're being abused (even after the relationship ends). ¶

october, dv awareness month, came and went and i felt the heaviness of being a full year gone from my home church, the place i dreamed of raising a family. the creeping realization that i have become an "ex-church-goer" as i grapple for the first time with being alienated from my own faith and those who practice it. ¶

it has been a long, lonely, profoundly empty season. but i have become so curious about what church and faith must really mean apart from the modern church construct. i would love your prayers. | #silenceisnotspiritual #churchtoo #metoo

also, i’m editing this to add that we’re not somehow cured or totally healed or something. that’s not a thing. 
#survivor #metoo #partnership

f! inrättar minnesdag för patriarkatets offer 
ett år har passerat sedan #metoo slog ner i sverige. alla var överens. det var oacceptabelt, åtgärder måste vidtas.
men, som oftast i frågor som rör jämställdhet och feminism, är steget från ord till handling oerhört långt. ett antal symboliska justeringar gjordes i regeringens budget, däremot lyser genomgripande reformer eller myndighetsdirektiv med sin frånvaro.

istället är det just nu snarare en backlash som sticker ut mest i det offentliga samtalet. debatten domineras av kränkta män, en nyväckt konservativ våg av röster som drömmer om hemmafrutillvaro och okunnigt hummande om ”genusflum”, samt den återkommande häpnadsväckande åsikten att ”det har gått för långt”, med #metoo, med jämställdheten, med mänskliga rättigheter.

som om vittnesmålen försvunnit i en kollektiv minnesförlust. feministiskt initiativ har inte glömt. därför gör vi nu den 8 november till en nationell minnesdag och dedicerar hela månaden november till att minnas, hedra och visa uppskattning för de många metoo-uppropen”, skriver gita nabavi och gudrun schyman. →läs hela artikeln här: https://www.svt.se/opinion/vi-kommer-att-ga-sa-langt-som-det-kravs?fbclid=iwar2hqhk2zb0xczynoa4ww-3wzvsr1o9lxmpk_oehjjdu6i62jfpxcoyp-yw

text:
you heard of street harassment? well this is store harassment.

every time a female server comes into the restaurant i work at, the all male staff working by the entrance whistles and comments on how the girl looks. 
psychologically this fucks with us because we’re now spending extra time overthinking our outfit for just walking into our workplace that ya men made into a whole event when it shouldn’t be!

women should be dressing for themselves not for the approval of others. 
fyi:  cat calling is not a compliment.

#serverstellall #servers #waiter #waitress #fashion #metoo #metoomovement #catcalling #host #bartender #foodindustry #feminism #feminist #customersbelike #serverlife

text:
remember their names, they’ll be around a while. american history was made in the midterm elections last night, with a record 100+ women elected to congress. these fresh new faces are a spark of re-energized hope and inspiration in a political climate that’s been traditionally contained by the status quo. exciting things to come in 2019. 
alexandria ocasio-cortez • youngest woman ever elected to congress at 29
⚡️
ilhan omar • first somali-american, and one of first ever muslim women elected
✨
rashida tlaib • first palestinian-american, and first muslim alongside ilhan omar to be elected
⚡️
sharice davids • first lgbt native american women elected
✨
deb haaland • one of first native american women elected
⚡️
ayanna pressley • first black woman to be elected to congress by massachusetts
✨
jahana hayes • first black woman to be elected to congress by connecticut

text:
trauma effects us in unimaginable ways. it feels as if you step outside of yourself and watch as you deteriorate. i had lost all control. within a couple of months i gained 40 pounds. it’s almost been three years and i’m so damn proud of myself. you bet your sweet ass i took all of my power back. but healing is a hell of a journey that never ends. so no matter what it is you’re going through be sure to talk about the tough stuff, check on your friends, and check in with yourself 🧘🏻‍♀️
•••
self care is about forgiving yourself. it’s about acknowledging your progress and not putting yourself down if you fall off the wagon. and it’s about continuing to grow and continuing to heal. it’s also about eating that donut because why the hell not 🍩
#averagejill

text:
يبدو أن استعداد الأشخاص في الأماكن العامة لتقديم الإسعافات الأولية لنساء أصبن بنوبة قلبية قد يتأثر بشكل ملحوظ، خوفاً من تهمة التحرش.

نشرت صحيفة "ديلي تلغراف" دراسة جديدة أظهرت أن احتمال حصول المرأة على الإسعافات الأولية أقل من الرجال في مثل هذه الحالات.

وبعد حملة #metoo التي اجتاحت العالم، طرح الباحثون أسئلة على عشرات الأشخاص المدربين على تقديم الإسعافات الأولية، حول استعدادهم لإنقاذ الإناث المصابات بنوبات قلبية، وهو الأمر الذي يتطلب تدليك القلب.

وتركزت الإجابات حول عدة نقاط أبرزها الخوف من أن توجه لهم تهمة التحرش الجنسي بالمصابات، والقلق من أن عملية الإسعاف تستدعي تدليك منطقة الثدي. كما أشار البعض إلى أن النساء يملن إلى تهويل آلامهن أو تزييفها.

وكانت دراسات سابقة قد أظهرت أن نسبة 45 بالمائة من الرجال يتلقون الإسعافات الأولية في حال إصابتهم بنوبة قلبية، مقابل 39 بالمائة من النساء.

text:
wylie said that bannon's plans began to solidify in 2014, when cambridge analytica consulted various republican campaigns and pacs ahead of the midterm elections. the company began to test and apply its psychographics by using facebook data to model individuals' personality types in order to understand how to influence them.

documents show the john bolton super pac, which promoted candidates supported by recently appointed white house national security adviser john bolton, paid cambridge analytical $454,700 in 2014 for "behavioral microtargeting with psychographic messaging." those services included strategies that broke individual voters into "clusters" based on what messages would resonate with them.

wylie also said the company used focus groups and messaging trials in 2014 to test some of the concepts that became core themes of the trump campaign, such as "drain the swamp" and imagery of walls. "a lot of the narratives of the trump campaign were what we were testing in 2014," wylie said.

he added that bannon directly presided over much of the company's initial research. "everything that we were doing ultimately had to be passed up to bannon for approval," said wylie, who left the company in late 2014.

wylie said bannon would fly to london about once a month for company meetings, and during that time he came to understand bannon's ideology. "he really liked the idea of using a military-style approach to changing people's perceptions," wylie said.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan & drew griffin
cnn

text:
bannon wanted to use the sorts of aggressive messaging tactics usually reserved for geopolitical conflicts to move the us electorate further to the right, wylie said. he had already directed a series of anti-establishment, conservative documentary films and presided over the far-right website breitbart news, but cambridge analytica would mark another step in his overall ambitions to transform the nation.

with financial backing from hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer, bannon co-founded cambridge analytica in 2013 as the us-branch of strategic communication laboratories (scl) group, a british company that advertises how it has conducted "behavioral change" programs in more than 60 countries.

wylie described cambridge analytica as - steve bannon and robert mercer using a foreign, military contractor ... to use some of the same techniques that the military uses ... on the american electorate.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan and drew griffin
cnn

text:
hey friends! how are you right now? i want to talk to you all about my personal healing journey only for a bit. 2 years ago, a lot of you started following my journey on here. it was during a time in my (relatively short) life where i was feeling super empowered and shared a lot about my abuse, my traumas and overcoming them. i'm at a different point in my journey and it is one where i feel less inclined to share the details yet at the same time more inspired to speak up... but haven't figured out how that works for me. what that means for me, how i move in this world as a survivor. am i loud and proud? or am i a humble warrior? ... i'm in no rush to find a resolve. i'm more interested in exploring my resistance to letting go of my survivor story. the spiritual books i'm reading are helping me to come to a deeper understanding of suffering. how suffering is a part of the totality of our human experience. how letting go of the stories i build up around my personal suffering will free me from being bound to the suffering. how i might even be able to open to all the feelings and emotions suffering brings about and instead of identifying as them... be able to observe them as they come and as they eventually go. perhaps i'm opening to suffering right this very moment.

this weekend i've been given the gracious gift of being able to attend a 3 day intensive training yoga to transform trauma lead by @catherineaashton ... i'm not quite sure i have words to articulate how grateful i am.

thank you to all of you for your continued love and support. you have no idea how much your comments, messages and conversations have helped me move forward the past few years. even though social media can be tricky when it comes to mental health, i truly enjoy our space here together. i learn from all of you and can't thank you enough. i don't think i'd be where i am just yet without our time together here... now i'm rambling... i love you... i appreciate you! i will be present and open this weekend so i can continue on my path and hopefully hold healing space for others with more compassion and understanding.

#yogatotransformtrauma #healingjourney #metoo #yogaheals #humanexperience

text:
i look at her
i see her innocence 
i see how she looks at the world 
with an astonished look on her face
she’s pure 
innocent 
i look at her and i see myself 
i look at her i say “i will fight for you no matter what
i will believe you i won’t turn my back on you
i will try to protect you as much as i can 
i don’t want anything bad to happen you 
i won’t sweep anything under the rug 
i will always always be here for you
i love you”
i’m trying to be someone that i 
myself needed when i was younger
i will be that person who will be there for her
i see her eyes glow with innocence and i think to myself 
why, why would anyone want to ruin something that is so perfect and pure
she’s an angel 
i will protect her 
i will be there for her 
i’m going to show her that she is in control of her own body 
it’s hers to keep
i will teach her that there will be someone who will try to claim her body
there will be someone who ignores the word no
but i will teach her to fight back 
i will teach her to always fight for what she believes in 
you’re going to have a voice 
no one is allowed to steal your voice 
and if somehow they manage to steal your 
voice body soul 
we will fight together for what belongs to you my love
i will fight for you always
-denise⛈

text: nine years ago, my life changed forever when i was assaulted by someone i knew. i have spent 9 years dealing with the aftermath of that moment. my mental health has suffered, i have lost friends, and i was retraumatized when i tried to get justice for what happened. for the last 9 years i have dreaded this day, because despite how long it’s been, there are still days when it feels like it just happened. there is no moral here and i have no answers. it does get better, but somedays it gets so much worse. all i know, is this morning i was in tears and this evening i ran 6 miles. what happened to me will never be ok but i am so much stronger than i was, and no one can take that away from me. #metoo #shecanandshedid

text: this is how psychotherapy for depression changes the brain. in recent years, researchers have sought to look under the hood to understand the neural correlates of the changes brought about by psychotherapy. not only can such understanding help us hone in on the precise processes that are being acted upon in therapy, thus helping us focus on these gains, they could also show where pharmacological interventions might be complementary, and where they could directly obstruct the therapeutic work. now a systematic review and meta-analysis in psychiatry research: neuroimaging has outlined all we know so far about how therapy changes the depressed brain, and it suggests key changes occur in emotional processing areas. https://youwillbearwitness.com/2018/11/07/this-is-how-psychotherapy-for-depression-changes-the-brain/ #ptsd #ptsdawareness #peterfox #ptsdsurvivor #ptsdrecovery #trauma #stopracism #stopbullying #stopchildabuse #metoo #cardinalpell #youwillbearwitness #erinfado #therapydog

text:
work done by the lovely @emmajdde • accepting work from creatives hit us up at consent.self.movement@gmail.com 🖤 “ i have known too many people who have been taken advantage of while intoxicated. too many who were conned or guilt-tripped into having sex on one night stands and even with ex partners/partners.
 i personally have had my 'no' ignored, even on my old school bus by someone who always intimidated me. 
someone very close to me, was ignored when she said 'no'...she said no to her father. 
the lack of consent, it ruins lives. leaves devastating pain and can deeply affect mental, emotional and physical health, longterm. why is no one talking about it?
it needs to be known it doesn't count as consent if anyone is made afraid or anxious to say no. 
any type of clothing... or no clothing at all, that doesn't mean consent. intoxication doesn't mean consent. silence doesn't mean consent. involuntary advances that aren't consented to aren't ever appreciated. consent is enthusiastic, ongoing, freely given, sober, verbal and so important.” - @emmajdde

text:
susan j barron’s portrait series depicting the invisible: american veterans suffering from ptsd was among the most powerful retrospectives i’ve ever seen in my entire life. the soldier pictured here was raped by a “star soldier” and then found herself having to serve under him on the battlefield. it was altogether heartbreaking and inspiring knowing these brave souls keep trying to move forward with their lives, shattered as they may be ... “i am deployed with my rapist. i am sworn to do my duty as a medic. but i cannot bear to save this guy who raped me.“ gutted.
.

text:
the air is crisp
light rain trickling 
city lights guide her safely ⠀ ⠀ ⠀ her family and friends 
know where she will be 
a text before hand 
a text in the uber 
a text when she’s free 
she drinks to get tipsy 
stops when she reaches 3 
wears long pants and a 
conservative tee 
dances with her friends 
but not too sexually 
doesn’t make eye contact 
with the boy watching her attentively 
she keeps on dancing
she’s never felt more free 
she leaves the bar at 11pm ⠀ ⠀“just before 12” she thinks, reassuringly 
she only just makes it 
knuckles gripped with keys 
ripped jeans 
crying 
raped
stabbed.
little did she know 
about the invisible sign ⠀ ⠀ ⠀ women hold above their head 
that says 
rape me. ⠀ ⠀ ⠀ ⠀ ⠀ ⠀ ⠀ ⠀ ⠀#poetry #poems #women #art #poetryslam #instapoems #ibelieveher #spokenword #poetrycommunity #metoo #buttonpoetry #writing #writingsociety

text:
hey yogis, november’s focus of the month: big brother is watching you!
.
in this age of social media, we trade privacy for “connectedness,” but do we need to draw a line?
.
i love meeting like-minded people locally and from around the world here. i am also triggered by a miami practice of photographing/filming and posting students during class.
.
#davidlife says in this #fotm, “in yoga class the group is meant to give relief from the internet of things, and allow the doors of perception to open. yoga practice is a dialogue between god and the devotee.”
.
what is the role of social media in the yoga community? where do we draw the lines to prevent groupthink? to respect yoga as a spiritual practice? to honor those who get on their mat for healing and not exploitation?
. . .

text:
8 november 2018. new moon in scorpio 
what did you dream about last night? 
did it show you something that scares you?

dreams are a portal to the subconscious. the subconscious tries to communicate with us through our dreams. 
the reason i ask what you dreamt about is because it is likely to symbolically represent the fear or stress that is surfacing for release now. 
the scorpio new moon signifies a purge of negativity. a transformation of stressful energy. 
we can harness the new moon energy by banishing an old, destructive habit or two. 
to put it in perspective, both the sun (ego) and moon (emotions) are currently in the intense, dark and mysterious sign of scorpio. 
as we focus on the intense and dark emotions coming up, we really only have two options:

1. fear: hide, ignore, cower to, control or fear the darkness

2. love: see, face, forgive, love, heal and transform the darkness

it might sound hard. but nothing is more important.

these kind of powerful energies come in their own, divine timing. it is up to you whether you take their opportunities. 
this energy is a blessing in disguise. 
the more we work on healing and transforming the wounded parts of ourselves, the more secure we will feel and the more we can truly enjoy life. 
exposing pain and secrets is not a bad thing. think of the #metoo movement and australia’s dual-citizen politician purge. the more we expose it, the stronger and better-off we all are in the end. 
think of how you might transform or befriend the places in your mind that you avoid. 
a trick i have learned is to sit comfortably and bring up all the painful memories and feelings. as they come up, remind yourself that you have the power to transform this energy within you by affirming that you “clear and transmute it, in every space, time, dimension and reality”. healing really is that simple. be brave. be patient. have faith that the release will be worth it.

for each individual, the new moon will be triggering a different part of your chart/life. i would love to read your chart for anyone who would like some specific insight into this empowering energy. 
love and light ❤
l

text:
one year. it has been one whole year since i’ve opened up about being raped. 
one year. it has been one whole year of girls reaching out to me with prayers, #metoo stories, and just wanting to talk.
one year, of feeling a little freer, a little less pain and a lot of love.
•
two years, it’s been two years since i was raped.
two years of having to trust god through any situation.
two years of sometimes having really bad days where i can do nothing but cry. 
two years of fighting to make sure no girl ever has to go through what i went through.
• 
so, when people ask why i am so open to talk about sex, why i don’t have a filter, and tell me christians don’t speak how i do, i say no, the lack of education and speaking up is what keeps us in these cycles. i refuse to let other girl feel that they are alone, i refuse to not acknowledge that we need to educate our boys on consent, and i refuse to believe that my testimony and education won’t help somebody. •
even as i cry writing this, i know next year will be better than the past two.
•
if you haven’t already read my testimony it’s on my blog website! *link in bio*

text:
lo siento pero no me puedo quedar callada ante esto. como todos sabéis miss canadá y miss england han denunciado acoso sexual, pues bien, bélgica y cuba han desmentido esto.
y cómo siempre, me pregunto: ¿por qué siempre se duda de la víctima? que no te haya pasado a ti no significa que no le haya pasado a esas chicas. estamos en una sociedad que criminaliza a las víctimas de abusos en vez de pedir una explicación al presunto abusador. estamos en una sociedad que dice que avanza en derechos de la mujer pero somos las primeras en dudar de la otra, en descalificar a otra mujer, y mientras esto siga sucediendo no vamos a avanzar como sociedad, no vamos a conseguir la igualdad de la mujer. basta de abusos, violaciones y maltrato.
no digo que ese "señor" sea 100% culpable, tiene el derecho a que se piense en su inocencia. pero señores y señoras: nunca, jamás,se puede dudar y criminalizar a una mujer que dice haber sido una víctima de abuso/acoso, porque a todas nos puede ocurrir, porque debemos estar unidas.
y vuelvo a repetir: que no te haya pasado a ti, no significa que no le haya pasado a tu compañera. al menos dale el beneficio de la duda y muestrale tu apoyo.
espero una aclaración de la organización y que se tomen medidas, de lo contrario lxs missologxs tomaremos decisiones. 
no es no💪

text: i had to sit in the same courtroom all day with this creep, thank god my family was surrounded by my side, and i had the sweetest victims advocate to help me through it all. as women we must fight back, we cannot let vicious harassing stalking sickos ruin our lives, and make us live in fear. i'm so proud of myself today i stood up for myself and for what i believe in, i fought for my right for freedom, to be able to walk out my front door, walk my dog, go to the grocery store, go get my nails done, without fear of this sicko following me stalking me and praying on me. #metoo the last few years have been pure hell, this man mentally and physically almost robbed me of my soul. and today the judge put him in his place, and i win. now the permanent protection order is set in place for a year, he cannot come a thousand feet from me or my children or my mother. hopefully the devastation and destruction this man has done to me and my family is over. pray for me and my family tonight. not this sicko will leave us alone. and never hurt me again. women unite, don't let a man ever have that kind of fear and control held over your head. so proud of my baby girl testifying in court today, she was amazing. and my mom too. i was paralyzed in fear just being in the same room as him, i cried through my whole testimony, half of what i said i don't even remember, but i know the judge could see and feel my pain this man has caused me. you lose. women are strong. #we must stand up and fight for our right to be free of violence.thank you🖤🖤🖤🙏🙏🙏🙏 i will continue to fight for myself and fight for other women to be free of violence and verbal and physical and sexual abuse.sending all my love to those out there suffering right now, you can do it, you can follow the right legal steps, and get away from a terrible desperate situation. all my love and prayers...

text:
개인적으로 홍상수 감독 영화를 좋아해서 많이 본 편이다. 예전에 어떤 지인이 홍감독 영화는 픽션이 아니라 리얼리티라고 영화판 그대로라고 했는데, 요즘 영화판 미투를 보면 홍감독이 너무 현실을 미화를 시키지 않았나 싶다. 최근에 홍감독에게 실망한 부분이 많지만, 이와 별개로 드라마 “굿바이 솔로”나 영화 “화차”에서의 김민희씨의 캐릭터는 굉장히 각인되어 있는 편. 
i have enjoyed films of movie director, hong sangsoo. someone told me that he describes realities of film scene. however it seems like he beautified too much observing me too in korean film industry. i am kinda disappointed by director hong, yet the characters of kim minhee in “goodbye solo” and “helpless” were impressive.

text: progress isn’t linear. and everyday as i work on my struggle for self-love and healing, i gotta remind myself that my bad days and weeks don’t define me. i tried to keep everything in and just hurt myself more. i’m still learning to share with people my story and talk about everything i’ve been through. it makes me happy knowing that i’m not completely alone and have people who support me whether or not they realize it. no matter how hard i’ve struggled i’m glad i’ve come this far. part of this is realizing that i’ve also hurt other people. all i can do is put out more positivity than negativity and unlearn my toxic traits. i won’t stop working on my self improvement. #mentalhealthstruggles #abettermeiscoming #metoo #personal

text: aberrante, vergonzoso e intolerable. pocas palabras para definir la experiencia por la que han tenido que pasar las candidatas al miss tierra (miss earth) durante mínimo estos dos últimos años. recién terminada la edición de 2018, miss inglaterra @miss.earth.england miss canadá @missjaimeyvonne y miss guam @erma101 han hecho pública una denuncia por acoso sexual durante todo el certamen que duraba más de un mes y cuya organización es filipina. este certamen siempre fue tildado de turbio y oscuro, y el año pasado se desmontó el tongo con una cámara oculta. estas tres misses de este 2018 cuentan que los patrocinadores con la complicidad de la organización #missearth escribían a las chicas a sus móviles (pedían los números a la org) y las invitaban a islas privadas, a sus casas, a cenas en barcos y en sus casas, y muchas más barbaridades. y no era para hablar de lo mal que va la economía, no. era para lo que era. cuando estás chicas se negaban a ser seducidas por estos viejos (ellas empiezan a dar nombres en sus perfiles de instagram) y acudían a la organización está les robaba el pasaporte y las encerraba en habitaciones. haciéndolas sentir culpables de no se sabe qué. ignorando las durante la competencia. al parecer estos señores tienen mucho poder en filipinas, y nadie sabe qué precio se pagaba al.intentar escapar. cuentan que estaban literalmente cagadas de miedo. que vergüenza que en pleno siglo xxi suceda esto en una plataforma cómo es un certamen internacional. vergonzoso. ¿que te parece? #stopacososexual #ispageantnotsex #certamennoessexo #noestassola #metoo #missearthengland #missearthcanada  #missearthguam #acososexual #missearth #misstierra #basura #asco #verguenza #shame #ganasdevomitar #miedo #filipinas

text:
part i: a year ago today november 7, 2017, at 11:15am at my home in rankin county, i was raped. i said no, i said stop 🛑. why did this happen to me? the response from the man, “you know men sometimes do stupid things”. i felt so disgusted, wondering what to do next. out of my mind i decided to clean my body up, (blood was everywhere) before feeling the need to take my own life not knowing how to move pass that moment to live. so i decided to take numerous sleeping pills in hope that when i woke up it was all just a bad dream. however it wasn’t, it was real, very real. i tired to go about my day as though nothing happen until later within a 12 hour period after my assault i decided to go to the hospital. the embarrassment was real, i didn’t want to see a man but my room was filled with them ( doctors/nurses). do i stay or do i go is what i kept thinking.... ~ jm-myo voice
.
. -more to come each week of telling my story... .
.
.
.
