text_retweet:
#repost @feministerna with @get_repost
・・・
f! inrättar minnesdag för patriarkatets offer 
ett år har passerat sedan #metoo slog ner i sverige. alla var överens. det var oacceptabelt, åtgärder måste vidtas.
men, som oftast i frågor som rör jämställdhet och feminism, är steget från ord till handling oerhört långt. ett antal symboliska justeringar gjordes i regeringens budget, däremot lyser genomgripande reformer eller myndighetsdirektiv med sin frånvaro.

istället är det just nu snarare en backlash som sticker ut mest i det offentliga samtalet. debatten domineras av kränkta män, en nyväckt konservativ våg av röster som drömmer om hemmafrutillvaro och okunnigt hummande om ”genusflum”, samt den återkommande häpnadsväckande åsikten att ”det har gått för långt”, med #metoo, med jämställdheten, med mänskliga rättigheter.

som om vittnesmålen försvunnit i en kollektiv minnesförlust. feministiskt initiativ har inte glömt. därför gör vi nu den 8 november till en nationell minnesdag och dedicerar hela månaden november till att minnas, hedra och visa uppskattning för de många metoo-uppropen”, skriver gita nabavi och gudrun schyman. →läs hela artikeln här: https://www.svt.se/opinion/vi-kommer-att-ga-sa-langt-som-det-kravs?fbclid=iwar2hqhk2zb0xczynoa4ww-3wzvsr1o9lxmpk_oehjjdu6i62jfpxcoyp-yw

please write  rebootbernie.com  or  50gov.com  w/ more runoffs (esp. regionals)

florida
under fl state law, a recount is mandatory if the winning candidate’s
margin is less than 0.5 percentage points.
(r)holds a lead of 38,717 votes out of more than 8 million cast — a
margin of less than one half of 1 percent.
incumbent(d)sen. bill nelson & (r)rick scott

arizona (john mccain)
(r)lead of 17,240 votes out of more than 1.6 million cast — a margin
of roughly 1 percent.
~25 percent of votes in az are counted post election day.
(d)kyrsten sinema & (r)martha mcsally

montana
(r)lead of 6,082 votes out of more than 355,000 cast — a margin of
roughly 1.7 percent.
~66% of precincts counted
incumbent (d)jon tester & (r)matt rosendale

runoffs:
mississippi u.s. senator special election nov. 27 runoff
(d)mike espy 40.7% 359,687 & (r)cindy hyde-smith 41.5% 366,810

ga governor
(d)stacey abrams hopes for a runoff dec. 4 (since not 51%)
(d)stacey abrams 48.7% 1,906,257 & (r)brian kemp 50.4% 1,971,401

text:
today i wake up with joy, eagerness, and gratitude. these midterm elections demonstrated that representation, integrity, and respect matter. these elections showed that women, poc, queer, and immigrant communities matter and that  these communities create brilliant leaders. these elections proved that when we unite, we can make a difference- every vote creates impact. i am overcome with hope today- and this photo is just a small sample of the courageous people we have elected! to all that voted- thank you. to our newly elected leaders- thank you. to our ancestors that taught us to fight with courage- thank you. this is america. 
#midterms #elections #representation #representationmatters #imwithher #metoo #blackgirlmagic #feminism #intersectionalfeminism #vote

text:
today was so important. i could feel it as i walked towards the neighborhood polling station this afternoon.
👀 every single person i walked past made eye contact. every person of color shared that knowing nod. that, “we in this together sistah” head nod that i hadn’t seen so frequently since obama was running for office.
🙇🏾‍♀️if i was at all unsure, i’m now very certain... these are pressing times in our country. and as i cast my ballot today, i felt like i was doing it for every ancestor. every woman who was told to be quiet & sit down when all she needed... wanted was to be seen and heard. especially those whose voices had been prematurely snuffed out in hopes to quiet a community and those not granted the very human right to decide their life.
🙋🏾‍♀️today an african woman and citizen of america sauntered into the polls with a mission in mind, purpose in her heart and a voice to be heard. today she made her choice known. did you? #vote

text:
me tocaste,
me tocaste y me ensuciaste. 
derribaste mis esquemas, 
destrozaste mi mente. 
porque jugaste de más
con algo que nunca te quise dar.
y volviste tantas veces, 
no supe huir. 
pero te alejé de mí.

te juro
no podrás volver. 
que mis manos de niña
no pudieron, 
pero mi cabeza,
hoy,
es capaz.

te voy a derribar. 
nunca te amé, 
pero ahora lo entiendo, 
no te odiaré. 
no pienso callar, 
mi voz no la vas a tocar.

que hoy me reconstruyo
y te deconstruyo
te toca a ti huir. ¿a dónde vas a ir? 
el sistema se queda(ba) contigo. 
hoy el sistema lo monto yo.

#metoo es quizás el movimiento más importante del feminismo actual, las mujeres nos dimos cuanta de que a todas nos pasó, y que seguía pasando. que esto no se puede permitir, el abuso y el acoso sexual se tiene que acabar y es una de las luchas principales. tenemos ejemplos en nuestro país, como el de la manada, que dejan claro que vivimos en la cultura de la violación. pero ¿qué hacer para solucionarlo? yo lo tengo claro, leyes y educación.

text: idk how to explain this y’all. but last night was a huggggeee victory for houston and harris county. 27 year old latina immigrant lina hidalgo just became the most powerful democrat in texas. think of it like this, she is 2-3 time more powerful than the mayor of houston as she now over sees 4 million people and billions of dollars annually. she, like i did, took a leap of faith and ran against all odds. no one believed it could happen, but thanks to beto, #bluewave, and her dedication, she pulled it off!!! she beat unbeatable ed emmet!! you all know i write constantly about hispanic politics and the lack of representation - well, not only did we finally get a seat, we voted to put lina hidalgo in charge of the table!! guys i don’t know how else to explain this... i even busted out tears last night after seeing this.... someone please pinch me and wake me up if i’m dreaming!.... #historyinthemaking #yetshepersisted #history #houston #texas #hispanicpolitics #metoo #linahidalgo #linahidalgoforharriscounty #colombia #colombian #amidreaming #vote #electionsmatter

by the second half of the nineteenth century, with the rapid economic growth of the industrial revolution and the weakening of the patriarchal power of fathers, women began stepping outside the familial world into the public sphere, and joining the labor force in search of independent living. alongside housework, handicrafts, teaching and factories, women also filled creative positions such as journalism and fiction writing, and as performers in the theatrical stage. ⠀

text:
my anxiety is habitual.  i've been anxious for so long that i don't know how not to default into it.  i have been reminding myself that i'm not hiding anymore.  i've heard people talk about the "root" of emotional problems.  i guess i never really believed that by finding the root, i would heal.  i believe it now.  check out my letter where i revealed myself  in my bio.

text: it doesn’t matter how hard it is to pull myself out of bed or how battered my heart feels, or even how disappointed i am, i will always keep showing up for women. today i’m sharing a post about @wearegenderavengers (link in profile). this photo is from a panel i was on last year about how men can navigate and participate in life during, through, and after #metoo . @mrdougfrench put the panel together (not all of us are pictured in this photo by @mom2summit ). it had men and women, various ages and ethnicities. we had different viewpoints and actively learned from one another. it showed me in real time why we need more voices and faces. my post is about the experience of purposefully taking note of who we hear and see. there’s a cool, simple app to use. i’d love it if you clicked over and took a look. there are things we can do every single day to help reframe how we see the world and what needs work. the post is sponsored, but as ever, i am my unfiltered, passionate self.

text:
.
it's terribly frightening when i am doing everything according to the book and yet my symptoms continue to multiply. the disease has been advancing for at least 11 years. some days standing up or turning on a fawcet leaves me injured for weeks.
.
i've been thinking of starting this account for a while now. unsure how i feel about it but i need a place to talk about lyme and life. a place where support can be shared. a place where i do enough, i have enough, i am enough. a place where i can let it all hang out. a place where i can meet and speak with other lyme warriors. a place where i can be sick and still express beauty. a place that accepts paradoxes, including me.
.
today i lit this incense in a moment of grief and gratitude. it's the day after midterm elections. for every loser there is a winner. the problem seems to be that the winners are winning too much. sharing is shrinking and fear is growing. globally we are seeing political extremism rise as we turn our back on issues concerning the protection of our soil, our water, our air, our wilderness, the atmosphere. this is not an easy time to recover from late stage lyme disease.
.
i lit a candle and incense this morning to give thanks. when in doubt, when in pain, i turn to gratitude. it hasn't always been like that for me, but my years in first nation sweat lodges gave me this practice and i am so grateful for that and to them.
.
sharing my gratitude prayer from this morning: thank you for the air in my lungs, thank you for the support from my husband, ruben, and faithful oracle, antoinette. thank you for the health that does exist in my body, my community, and our institutions. thank you for this spiritual practice. thank you for a computer and phone that works. thank you for a functioning vehicle. thank you for my nurturing home. thank you for bell hooks and the voices of courage and uplift. thank you for my creative gifts. thank you for the miracle of life i have lived.
.
ps i just coughed and peed on the couch. fun times in the life of a lyme bodie!
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
#doyouseeme #doyouseememovement #visiblewomen #lymedisease #lymediseaseawareness #lyme #lymewarrior #lymeawareness

text:
.
it's terribly frightening when i am doing everything according to the book and yet my symptoms continue to multiply. the disease has been advancing for at least 11 years. some days standing up or turning on a fawcet leaves me injured for weeks.
.
i've been thinking of starting this account for a while now. unsure how i feel about it but i need a place to talk about lyme and life. a place where support can be shared. a place where i do enough, i have enough, i am enough. a place where i can let it all hang out. a place where i can meet and speak with other lyme warriors. a place where i can be sick and still express beauty. a place that accepts paradoxes, including me.
.
today i lit this incense in a moment of grief and gratitude. it's the day after midterm elections. for every loser there is a winner. the problem seems to be that the winners are winning too much. sharing is shrinking and fear is growing. globally we are seeing political extremism rise as we turn our back on issues concerning the protection of our soil, our water, our air, our wilderness, the atmosphere. this is not an easy time to recover from late stage lyme disease.
.
i lit a candle and incense this morning to give thanks. when in doubt, when in pain, i turn to gratitude. it hasn't always been like that for me, but my years in first nation sweat lodges gave me this practice and i am so grateful for that and to them.
.
sharing my gratitude prayer from this morning: thank you for the air in my lungs, thank you for the support from my husband, ruben, and faithful oracle, antoinette. thank you for the health that does exist in my body, my community, and our institutions. thank you for this spiritual practice. thank you for a computer and phone that works. thank you for a functioning vehicle. thank you for my nurturing home. thank you for bell hooks and the voices of courage and uplift. thank you for my creative gifts. thank you for the miracle of life i have lived.
.
ps i just coughed and peed on the couch. fun times in the life of a lyme bodie!
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.

text:
la discriminación es toda aquella acción u omisión realizada por personas, grupos o instituciones, que produce y reproduce desigualdades en el acceso a recursos y oportunidades tan difíciles como comida, servicios de salud, educación o empleo, en favor o en contra de un grupo social y sus miembros. es el acto de separar o formar grupos de personas a partir de criterios determinados. se refiere a la violación de la igualdad de los derechos humanos por cuestiones sociales, raciales, religiosas, de orientación sexual de género o su preferencia sexual. 
tipos de discriminación

los tipos de discriminación más frecuentes

1- racismo.

2-discriminación por nacionalidad u origen étnico.

3.discriminación por orientación sexual

4-discriminación por género.

5-discriminación de la mujer en el trabajo.

6-discriminación por maternidad.

7-discriminación por edad.

8-discriminación laboral

nuestra opinión:

nosotros no estamos de acuerdo con la discriminación, ya que no debes cuestionar ni ser cuestionado por nadie. nadie debe juzgar a nadie por sus apariencias físicas, por su forma de pensar, por sus principios, por su nacionalidad, sexo u orientación sexual... y es también algo muy desagradable pues todos somos iguales, el color de piel, el sexo, el idioma u otras cosas no hacen diferentes, todos nos tenemos que respetar, tratarnos con equidad. antes de hablar mal de alguien, siempre hay que fijarse en uno mismo. "los hombres nacen libres e iguales y mueren en ese estado"

text:
une sortie après un mois sans courir. pourquoi ? juste parceque je voulais profiter de chaque instants avec mon fils et notre famille.
mais toujours avec du renforcement musculaire et avec mon bébé sa complique un peu lol.
.
la sortie se passer très bien jusqu'à ce que je fasse une mauvaise rencontre...
quand on dis qu'on ne peux plus courir seule en étant tranquille, sans regarder derrière soi... aujourd'hui il est clair que je vais pas retourner courir seule, en club ou juste faire la connaissance d'autres coureurs mais plus seule...
j'ai hésiter à publier ce message mais je pense qu'il est important car sa n'arrive pas qu'aux autres...
faites attention à vous et courrais accompagner.

text:
let’s talk body image. something i have struggled with since high school. i was always the “too skinny” one. i got called chicken legs, olive oil, deer legs.. you name it. i never would wear shorts up until i moved to florida in 2009 and it was just too hot to not wear them 😂. i stopped caring what people thought cause i needed to be comfortable. but deep down i still felt “too skinny.” the last 8 years i had lost about 10-15 pounds and at one point even got under 100lbs. i’m almost 5’8”. i looked sick. it’s amazing what stress does to our bodies. i lost my period during that time. it was not a pleasurable time to say the least. i made a stand with myself to never let myself sink back into that state. it has been a challenge to keep weight on. stress screws up your hormones which contribute to weight control, like your thyroid. and people show it in different forms. i know there are others out there like me. struggling with weight or your body image. know you are not alone! today i make a pledge to myself to stay strong and take control! weed out your stressors. keep yahweh close. eat healthy. and stay in the gym. ignore people that tell you to eat a hamburger or to not. they don’t know that has an opposite emotional effect on someone. and people, think twice before telling someone to go eat. instead, give words of encouragement like, you are looking beautiful today! that is encouragement! 🙌🏼 stay strong my warrior friends! you are not alone. .
.
.
.
#metoo #youarenotalone #warrior #strong #rise #inspire #fitness #overcomer #health #tinybutmighty #gratitude
